    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 30th with a potent offensive outlook, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez**, who commands our highest efficiency score of 82.97. His matchup against Young (4.67 xERA) is the day's primary target, bolstered by a massive 16% park adjustment and an elite 0.393 projected xwOBA. **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** also offer significant upside against Houser (4.46 xERA); while Houser\u2019s secondary stuff creates a slight dynamic platoon drag, the sheer volume of plate appearances at the top of the order keeps both well within the \"Strong\" start tier. **Colt Keith** rounds out our primary group with a 62.32, benefiting from a favorable 4.29 xERA matchup and a prime #3 hole placement.\n\nWhile our bench remains relatively thin due to the off-days for **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Junior Caminero**, and **Caleb Durbin**, **Jerar Encarnacion** provided the most difficult personnel decision. He fell just short of our mandatory 40.0 floor with a 39.79 score. Despite a favorable platoon edge, he is stymied by a tough matchup against S\u00e1nchez (3.02 xERA) and a suboptimal #8 spot in the lineup, making him a clear fade to preserve our daily games-played cap. **Kazuma Okamoto** and **Carson Benge** maintain their utility roles despite marginal scores hovering near 60; they are elevated by strong skill-based advantages against their respective opposing starters, provided they can navigate the risks inherent in their matchups against Ober and Mikolas. We will continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Zac Veen**, **Luke Raley**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Josh Smith**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Luis Pena**, and **Pedro Ramirez** as we manage our remaining caps for the month.",
